ARMatura: hardware/software embedded platform and large book (in russian)
designed for SSAU ASCL Aerospace Construction Institute

by (c) Dmitry Ponyatov <dponyatov@gmail.com>, OpenHardware & LGPL lic.

Based on faster Cortex-M microcontroller architecture in place of
Atmel AVR8 and Arduino usage in laboratory and space experiments.

Widely available for public usage in terms of OpenHardware and LGPL licence
with some limits in area of SSAU ASCL internal applications.

It's yet another replacement of Arduino platform
equipped with large manual (ru).

The goal is providing good basis for students and science personal
not adopted to real embedded developent.
 
 